# GSAP (Soft Gift storytelling)

Primary motion for marketing / scroll / PDP / Build-Your-Box. Framer Motion only for tiny UI presence. **Do not** animate cart qty, pay button, or admin tables with heavy timelines.

## Required setup

```tsx
'use client';
import { useGSAP } from '@gsap/react';
import gsap from 'gsap';
import { ScrollTrigger } from 'gsap/ScrollTrigger';

if (typeof window !== 'undefined') gsap.registerPlugin(ScrollTrigger);

// inside component — scope to ref; useGSAP cleans up on unmount/route change
useGSAP(() => {
  gsap.from('.hero-title', { opacity: 0, y: 16, duration: 0.45 });
}, { scope: containerRef });
```

| Do | Don't |
|---|---|
| Client leaf only | `gsap.*` during SSR/render |
| Scope selectors to a container `ref` | Global `'.card'` across the app |
| `transform` + `opacity` | Animate `top/left/width/height` (unless Flip) |
| `next/dynamic` + `ssr: false` for heavy scenes | Ship GSAP on checkout bundle “just in case” |

## Reduced motion

If `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce` → skip pin/scrub/parallax; keep final content visible; **never** hide CTA / price / stock behind opacity 0.

## Hydration

Server and client JSX must match. Don’t branch markup on `window`. Animate after mount only.

## Merge checklist

- [ ] `useGSAP` scoped · [ ] reduced-motion path · [ ] no SSR crash · [ ] mobile pin sane/off · [ ] LCP image not delayed by fade-in · [ ] CTAs clickable during/after
